# Security Rules

## Secrets
- NEVER hardcode API keys, tokens, or passwords
- Use --dart-define for compile-time configuration
- Use flutter_secure_storage for runtime secrets
- SharedPreferences is NOT secure — never store tokens there

## Logging
- NEVER log authentication tokens or credentials
- NEVER log PII (emails, phone numbers, names)
- NEVER log full HTTP request/response bodies in production
- Use structured logging with severity levels

## Network
- HTTPS only — no HTTP exceptions
- Validate all deep link URLs before navigation
- Sanitize user input before display or transmission

## Dependencies
- Audit for vulnerabilities monthly
- No packages with known security issues
